column16: [{"dateSeen":"2024-08-22T04:44:00.000Z","value":"Four property portfolio located in three states-- Illinois, New Jersey and Texas.​   The portfolio includes: ​Chase Bank and Walgreens in Chicago, IL ​Advance Auto in Fanwood, NJ ​Mattress Firm | Red Cross in Irving, TX Average Term Remaining: 6.88 years"},{"dateSeen":"2024-08-25T09:27:00.000Z","value":"Jones Lang LaSalle Americas, Inc.​ (“JLL”) is pleased to offer the opportunity to acquire the ground lease interest in a freestanding single-tenant Chase Bank located at 488 W Liberty Street in Wauconda, IL.​ This Asset features an investment grade corporate guaranty from JPMorgan Chase Bank (S&P: ‘A-’) and is operating on a 20-year absolute triple net lease with zero landlord responsibilities and four, five-year renewal options.​ Notably, the Tenant reported $181.3M in deposits in 2022, which represents an outstanding 80% deposit growth since 2017.​ Located 45 miles northwest of downtown Chicago, the Property is positioned in a highly affluent suburb with access to over 70,000 residents in a five-mile radius.​ The Property’s retail submarket, Central Northwest, boasts 14.5 million square feet of inventory and is supply constrained with 6.3% vacancy.​ The submarket performs exceptionally well with 10.9% rent growth since 2019.​ Situated across from Liberty Square Shopping Center, the area has attracted notable national tenants including Jewel-Osco, Tractor Supply, Dollar Tree, and Ace Hardware, among many others.​ This rare opportunity allows investors the ability to acquire a high performing bank branch located in a fundamentally strong and affluent Chicago suburb.​ The asset offers secure, long-term cash flow backed by one of the world’s largest financial institutions.​"}]

column16: [{"dateSeen":"2024-04-16T09:50:00.000Z","value":"ABOUT THE TENANT:Berkshire Health Systems is the leading provider of comprehensive healthcare services for residents and visitors to Berkshire County. From inpatient surgery and cancer care to provider visits and imaging, Berkshire Health Systems (BHS) offers a continuum of programs and services that help patients to connect to the care they need, no matter where they are located in the rural Berkshire community. BHS supports 24-hour emergency care at its two inpatient acute care facilities, Berkshire Medical Center (BMC) in Pittsfield and Fairview Hospital in Great Barrington, as well as the Satellite Emergency Facility on the BMC campus in North Adams. Their hospitals offer advanced imaging and lab services and are closely integrated with the specialty care provided at the BMC Cancer Center. Berkshire Visiting Nurses Association (BVNA), BHS Urgent Care Center, and the BHS medical group network of primary and specialty care providers extend their continuum of expert care beyond the hospital. BHS offers its broad range of award-winning services at 30 provider clinics with 48 office locations across the county. As the largest employer in Berkshire County, BHS supports more than 4,000 jobs in the region, and, as a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization, BHS is committed to partnering with local municipalities and community organizations to help the county thrive. LOCATION:Pittsfield is the largest city and the county seat of Berkshire County, Massachusetts. It is the principal city of the Pittsfield, Massachusetts Metropolitan Statistical Area which encompasses all of Berkshire County. The population was 43,927 at the 2020 census. Pittsfield remains the third largest municipality in Western Massachusetts. As the commercial center of the Berkshires, Pittsfield is the home of the world headquarters of SABIC Innovative Plastics, Berkshire Life, and General Dynamics Defense Systems center. Forward-thinking entrepreneurs have been investing and growing in Pittsfield, including Interprint’s $7 million capital investment, LTI Smart Glass’ $5 million expansion, the redesign of Pittsfield Plaza, and the long-anticipated Beacon Cinema on North St. Pittsfield is also the financial center of the Berkshires, as home to the ever-growing Berkshire Bank, Pittsfield Cooperative Bank, Greylock Federal Credit Union, and Berkshire Life. It has an estimated population of 81,252, making it the twelfth largest city in Michigan. Genesee County has a population of 425,790, making it the fifth-most populous county in Michigan. The county seat and population center is Flint (birthplace of General Motors). Genesee County is considered to be a part of the greater Mid Michigan area. Genesee County comprises the Flint, MI Metropolitan Statistical Area and is included in the Detroit-Warren-Ann Arbor, MI Combined Statistical Area. Genesee County is located in the midst of the I-69 International Trade Corridor, a major distribution route with interstate access to Detroit, Chicago and Canada-to-Mexico connections, along with Bishop International Airport and rail service. The county’s location and diverse activities offers low cost-of-living without sacrificing cultural amenities or outdoor recreation. The immediate area offers top-notch hospitals and world renowned education centers. A major attraction for visitors is Crossroads Village, a living history village opened in 1976. It is operated by the Genesee County Parks and Recreation Commission alongside the Huckleberry Railroad. Crossroads Village is home to 34 buildings, many which are restored 19th-century buildings, as well as amusement rides, a narrow-gauge railroad, and a replica paddlewheel steamboat. leased, newly-renovated, freestanding Voodoo Doughnut investment property located in Katy, Texas (Houston MSA).​ The tenant, Voodoo Doughnut, LLC, recently signed a brand new 15-year lease with 2 (5-year) options to extend, demonstrating their commitment to the site.​ The lease features 10% rental increases every 5 years throughout the initial term and at the beginning of each option period, growing NOI and hedging against inflation.​ Under the NNN lease, the tenant is responsible for taxes, insurance, and utilities, and maintains all aspects of the Premises, including roof & structure.​ Landlord responsibilities are limited to building insurance (see pg 19 for details), making this an ideal, low-management investment opportunity for a passive investor.​ Voodoo Doughnut is a growing, vegan-friendly donut brand with over 15 locations in six different states.​ The newly renovated building opened in November, 2022, becoming the fourth Voodoo Doughnut location in the greater Houston area.​ Voodoo Doughnut is strategically located along Fry Road, which averages 52,600 vehicles passing by daily.​ The site benefits from nearby direct on/off ramp access to Interstate 10, the main east-west highway serving the southern United States averaging nearly 276,000 vehicles per day.​ Furthermore, the building is equipped with a 24-hour drive-thru, providing ease and convenience for guests.​ On average, stores with drive-thrus experience higher sales than those without.​ The subject property is ideally situated as an outparcel to Price Plaza, a regional power center anchored by Walmart Supercenter and Ross Dress for Less.​ In addition, the asset is directly across from Westgate Marketplace, a 300,000 SF center anchored by H-E-B, the top grocery store brand in Texas.​ The Walmart and H-E-B average a combined 3.5 million annual visits (placer.​ai).​ Other nearby national/credit tenants include The Home Depot, Target, Lowe’s Home Improvement, T.​J.​ Maxx, Kohl’s, Sam’s Club, Hobby Lobby, and many more.​ Strong tenant synergy increases consumer draw to the immediate trade area and promotes crossover store exposure to the site.​ The 5-mile trade area is supported by over 275,000 residents and nearly 87,000 employees, providing a direct consumer base from which to draw.​ Residents within 5 miles of the subject property boast an affluent average household income of It offers the opportunity to homestead, a beautiful area for a plentiful garden to grow your own food, a large pole barn reattached garage to work on your equipment and store it away, and a large barn that offers plenty of opportunities to house your livestock in comfort. To add it is located on a low traffic blacktop road within 2 miles of Ohio 7 S. And what comes to mind when we begin to talk about the house? Well, the word is nostalgia. This place may need a little elbow grease, but I've been around this county my whole life, and I've seen a lot of these farmhouse-style homes, and they just provide primitive charm that can't be duplicated. This place is in great shape for a rehab to make it into that big dream home. While the way it sits, it's more than livable, offering tons of charm, main-level living, a main-level office, and two additional upstairs bedrooms. Plus, the house features main level laundry and one full bathroom, adding to its convenience. If you are looking for a weekend getaway, this one could stand true to being that base camp hunting lodge or that weekend getaway as well. It's just beautiful out here at 763 Swan Creek. Country living at its finest! You cant beat the setting for this two-story home accompanied with two barns and 60 acres to enjoy all to yourself. Dont miss out on this opportunity to walk out your front door and enjoy everything nature has to offer. A perfect place to enjoy your morning coffee and listen to the world come alive. Surrounding the house is approx. 3.5 acres of fenced in pasture, perfect for livestock or gardening. The road frontage on this property equals out to be roughly 1400, with frontage on both sides of the road. The two acres of open/flat across from the house could be sold off separately for income. The two-story home with utilities on site includes 3 BR and 1 bath, with a poured concrete porch and and 27 x 36 metal building. Plenty of space for vehicles and other equipment such as tractors or atvs. Swan creek, which flows year-round, runs directly through the property. Swan creek road itself is very private, with little through traffic. Believe it or not everything weve already covered only makes up less than half the property! There is still 40+/- acres that we havent touched on. This section is mainly timber and is made up of rolling to steep terrain. This gives you access to excellent hunting, hiking, or trail riding the minute you step out your front door. As I made my way through the trail system, the abundant wildlife sign made it clear this place would be a no-brainer for anyone looking to manage their own property. The terrain changes and heavy foliage makes this a perfect sanctuary for big southern Ohio bucks to hideout in. There is a good variety of timber species, including white and red oak, hickory, poplar, and others native to Ohio. This property is situated less than 2 miles from the Ohio River and West Virginia border and would make a great deer camp for someone out of state. If WV and Ohio arent enough, Eastern Kentucky is also just a short trip, roughly 30 miles, allowing you opportunities to hunt in three different states all within an hour of your home. You truly cant beat everything this property has to offer for the price. Reach out to Realtree Land Pro Jason Williams today at 740-352-3691 for a showing!.
